The profitability index refers to the ratio between the present value of future cash inflows and the initial investment. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Profitability index}&=\dfrac{\frac{\text{present cash flow year 1}}{(1+r)^1}+\frac{\text{present cash flow year 2}}{(1+r)^2}+...+\frac{\text{present cash flow year 5}}{(1+r)^5}}{\text{Initial investment}}
\end{aligned}$$
